<subSubSection id="8294EDF05672FFBAFF77FD645AE0FCD3" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="CA31BE7B5672FFBAFF77FD645AE0FCD3" blockId="7.[151,1437,618,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFF77FD645949FD43" bold="true" box="[199,334,726,751]" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Etymology.</emphasis>
This name (f., noun in apposition) Comes from the Latin words, 
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFBE0FD655C94FD42" box="[1104,1171,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">verus,</emphasis>
meaning true and 
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFAC4FD655D9BFD42" box="[1396,1436,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">pax</emphasis>
meaning peaCe. It reCalls the Claim of the Colombian people for the end of the longest Civil war, whiCh has devastated the Country for deCades (i.e. 63 years). Moreover, it expresses the ConCern of the soCiety with the preservation of natural resourCes that were unreaChable and threatened due to this war in our territories; and Calls for our biggest hope: to aChieve a true state of peaCe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8294EDF05672FFBAFF77FC385CC2FA4F" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" type="description">
<paragraph id="CA31BE7B5672FFBAFF77FC385D28FC6B" blockId="7.[151,1437,618,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFF77FC3859E9FC0E" bold="true" box="[199,494,906,931]" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">
Description of 
<typeStatus id="153500D95672FFBAFE31FC3859EFFC0F" box="[385,488,906,931]" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFE4BFC385A30FC0F" box="[507,567,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Head</emphasis>
. Yellow, with greyish-yellow vertex, and two laterodorsal blaCk spots on labrum, posterior half of frons blaCk with two yellow spots behind lateral oCelli (
<figureCitation id="52B5A2FE5672FFBAFBAFFC1C5C76FC6B" box="[1055,1137,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cora verapax sp. nov. holotype: a. head and thorax in dorsal and lateral views respectively; b. genital ligula in ventral view; c. S10 and cercus in dorsal view; d. S9–10 and cercus in lateral view; e. habitus in lateral view. a-l. p.: apicolateral processes, f. l. l.: filamentous lateral lobes, m-l. p.: midlateral processes. Photos: a, c–e: CABS; b: Camilo Flórez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
). Frons rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA31BE7B5672FFBAFF77FC605AF5FB4B" blockId="7.[151,1437,618,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFF77FC60591FFC47" box="[199,280,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Thorax</emphasis>
. Prothorax: pronotum blue with middorsal blaCk stripe, posterior portion of median lobe blaCk, and posterior lobe blaCk margined blue (
<figureCitation id="52B5A2FE5672FFBAFD9DFC445A9EFBA3" box="[557,665,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cora verapax sp. nov. holotype: a. head and thorax in dorsal and lateral views respectively; b. genital ligula in ventral view; c. S10 and cercus in dorsal view; d. S9–10 and cercus in lateral view; e. habitus in lateral view. a-l. p.: apicolateral processes, f. l. l.: filamentous lateral lobes, m-l. p.: midlateral processes. Photos: a, c–e: CABS; b: Camilo Flórez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Fig. 4a, e</figureCitation>
); propleuron yellow (
<figureCitation id="52B5A2FE5672FFBAFC3CFC445BFFFBA3" box="[908,1016,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cora verapax sp. nov. holotype: a. head and thorax in dorsal and lateral views respectively; b. genital ligula in ventral view; c. S10 and cercus in dorsal view; d. S9–10 and cercus in lateral view; e. habitus in lateral view. a-l. p.: apicolateral processes, f. l. l.: filamentous lateral lobes, m-l. p.: midlateral processes. Photos: a, c–e: CABS; b: Camilo Flórez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Fig. 4a, e</figureCitation>
). Pterothorax: blue with blaCk stripes in middorsal Carina, mesepisternum and antehumeral suture, the latter expanding at its proximal portion surrounding the mesoCoxae (
<figureCitation id="52B5A2FE5672FFBAFE45FB8C5A74FBFB" box="[501,627,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cora verapax sp. nov. holotype: a. head and thorax in dorsal and lateral views respectively; b. genital ligula in ventral view; c. S10 and cercus in dorsal view; d. S9–10 and cercus in lateral view; e. habitus in lateral view. a-l. p.: apicolateral processes, f. l. l.: filamentous lateral lobes, m-l. p.: midlateral processes. Photos: a, c–e: CABS; b: Camilo Flórez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Fig. 4a, e</figureCitation>
); thin blaCk lines between mesepimeron and metepimeron and in metapleural suture, this one gets wider towards the posterior margin and toward its proximal portion surrounding the metaCoxae (
<figureCitation id="52B5A2FE5672FFBAFEFBFB3459BDFB33" box="[331,442,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cora verapax sp. nov. holotype: a. head and thorax in dorsal and lateral views respectively; b. genital ligula in ventral view; c. S10 and cercus in dorsal view; d. S9–10 and cercus in lateral view; e. habitus in lateral view. a-l. p.: apicolateral processes, f. l. l.: filamentous lateral lobes, m-l. p.: midlateral processes. Photos: a, c–e: CABS; b: Camilo Flórez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Fig. 4a, e</figureCitation>
); blaCk spot surrounding the metepimeral spiraCle. Venter gray with a tuberCle Close to abdomen base, posteriorly Covered with golden setae. Legs: Coxae grayish blue (Covered with pruinesCenCe when alive, 
<figureCitation id="52B5A2FE5672FFBAFF6BFB7C5942FB4B" box="[219,325,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cora verapax sp. nov. holotype: a. head and thorax in dorsal and lateral views respectively; b. genital ligula in ventral view; c. S10 and cercus in dorsal view; d. S9–10 and cercus in lateral view; e. habitus in lateral view. a-l. p.: apicolateral processes, f. l. l.: filamentous lateral lobes, m-l. p.: midlateral processes. Photos: a, c–e: CABS; b: Camilo Flórez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Fig. 4a, e</figureCitation>
), armature and legs blaCk (
<figureCitation id="52B5A2FE5672FFBAFDC4FB7C5AE2FB4B" box="[628,741,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cora verapax sp. nov. holotype: a. head and thorax in dorsal and lateral views respectively; b. genital ligula in ventral view; c. S10 and cercus in dorsal view; d. S9–10 and cercus in lateral view; e. habitus in lateral view. a-l. p.: apicolateral processes, f. l. l.: filamentous lateral lobes, m-l. p.: midlateral processes. Photos: a, c–e: CABS; b: Camilo Flórez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Figs 4a, e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA31BE7B5672FFBAFF77FB465C90FA83" blockId="7.[151,1437,618,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFF77FB46590DFAA7" box="[199,266,1268,1291]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Wings</emphasis>
. Membrane smoky Colored; venation and pterostigma blaCk; Px 
<quantity id="0D76139E5672FFBAFC5EFB415C2FFAA7" box="[1006,1064,1266,1291]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.906" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" unit="in" value="39.0">39 in</quantity>
FW, 
<quantity id="0D76139E5672FFBAFBD8FB415CCBFAA7" box="[1128,1228,1266,1291]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.747" metricValueMax="7.874" metricValueMin="7.62" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" unit="in" value="30.5" valueMax="31.0" valueMin="30.0">30–31 in</quantity>
HW; pt overlying six Cells; FW nodus Closer to the pterositgma (13.0mm) than to the base of wing (
<quantity id="0D76139E5672FFBAFB98FAA45C8CFA83" box="[1064,1163,1302,1327]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" unit="mm" value="14.5">14.5mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA31BE7B5672FFBAFF77FA885CC2FA4F" blockId="7.[151,1437,618,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFF77FA885936FAFF" box="[199,305,1338,1363]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Abdomen</emphasis>
. BlaCk exCept dorsum of S1 and anterior 2/3 of S2 dorsum whiCh are blue (
<figureCitation id="52B5A2FE5672FFBAFB14FA885D13FAFF" box="[1188,1300,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cora verapax sp. nov. holotype: a. head and thorax in dorsal and lateral views respectively; b. genital ligula in ventral view; c. S10 and cercus in dorsal view; d. S9–10 and cercus in lateral view; e. habitus in lateral view. a-l. p.: apicolateral processes, f. l. l.: filamentous lateral lobes, m-l. p.: midlateral processes. Photos: a, c–e: CABS; b: Camilo Flórez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Fig. 4a, e</figureCitation>
). S10 has a middorsal horn on apex, pointed in dorsoposterior direCtion (
<figureCitation id="52B5A2FE5672FFBAFCEAFAEC5BD6FADB" box="[858,977,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cora verapax sp. nov. holotype: a. head and thorax in dorsal and lateral views respectively; b. genital ligula in ventral view; c. S10 and cercus in dorsal view; d. S9–10 and cercus in lateral view; e. habitus in lateral view. a-l. p.: apicolateral processes, f. l. l.: filamentous lateral lobes, m-l. p.: midlateral processes. Photos: a, c–e: CABS; b: Camilo Flórez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Fig 4 C–d</figureCitation>
). Genital ligula with filamentous lateral lobes, small midlateral proCesses, and wide lateroapiCal projeCtions (
<figureCitation id="52B5A2FE5672FFBAFC2BFA305BE8FA37" box="[923,1007,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cora verapax sp. nov. holotype: a. head and thorax in dorsal and lateral views respectively; b. genital ligula in ventral view; c. S10 and cercus in dorsal view; d. S9–10 and cercus in lateral view; e. habitus in lateral view. a-l. p.: apicolateral processes, f. l. l.: filamentous lateral lobes, m-l. p.: midlateral processes. Photos: a, c–e: CABS; b: Camilo Flórez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
). CerCus tip Curving inwards in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="52B5A2FE5672FFBAFF53FA14593CFA13" box="[227,315,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1326,1348]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,520,1258]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,511,1270]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Colombian National System of Protected Areas (SINAP) including the register Civil Society Natural Reserves reported to the Ministry of Environment until 2015." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441440/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
), in lateral view almost straight with a midventral tooth (
<figureCitation id="52B5A2FE5672FFBAFC49FA145C54FA13" box="[1017,1107,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[206,1381,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cora verapax sp. nov. holotype: a. head and thorax in dorsal and lateral views respectively; b. genital ligula in ventral view; c. S10 and cercus in dorsal view; d. S9–10 and cercus in lateral view; e. habitus in lateral view. a-l. p.: apicolateral processes, f. l. l.: filamentous lateral lobes, m-l. p.: midlateral processes. Photos: a, c–e: CABS; b: Camilo Flórez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
). ParaproCts not developed. Measurements (mm). Total length 69.5, length of abdomen 57.1, FW 31.6 and HW 29.6 length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8294EDF05672FFBAFF77FA5C594FF877" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CA31BE7B5672FFBAFF77FA5C594FF877" blockId="7.[151,1437,618,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFF77FA5C5A92F9AB" bold="true" box="[199,661,1518,1543]" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">
Notes on the 
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFED1FA5C599CF9AA" bold="true" box="[353,411,1518,1542]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Cora</emphasis>
genus and diagnosis.
</emphasis>
The last phylogenetiC analysis (SánChez-Herrera 
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFB70FA5D5CFFF9AB" box="[1216,1272,1518,1543]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">et al.</emphasis>
2018) showed the genus 
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFEBDF9A15940F986" box="[269,327,1555,1578]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Cora</emphasis>
as traditionally grouped is polyphyletiC in the light of the genetiC evidenCe. The 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFB5FF9A65D37F987" baseAuthorityName="Selys" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[1263,1328,1556,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Polythoridae" genus="Cora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyane">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFB5FF9A65D37F987" box="[1263,1328,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">cyane</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFADCF9A65D9BF987" baseAuthorityName="Selys" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[1388,1436,1556,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Aeolagrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inca">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFADCF9A65D9BF987" box="[1388,1436,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">inca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="AE1FC38A5672FFBAFE32F9845A6FF9E3" box="[386,616,1590,1615]" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" refId="ref4441" refString="Bick, G. H. &amp; Bick, J. C. (1991) Two new damselflies: Cora dorada spec. nov. from Ecuador and C. parda spec. nov. from Peru (Zygoptera: Polythoridae). Odonatologica, 20 (4), 453 - 458." type="journal article">BiCk &amp; BiCk (1991)</bibRefCitation>
share several CharaCters but were separated beCause of the lateroapiCal projeCtions of the genital ligula observed in 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFD31F9E95B8BF9DF" authority="(Selys, 1873)" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1873" baseAuthorityName="Selys" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[641,908,1626,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Polythoridae" genus="Cora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inca">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFD31F9E95AF6F9DF" box="[641,753,1627,1651]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Cora inca</emphasis>
(Selys, 1873)
</taxonomicName>
. SánChez-Herrera 
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFBECF9EE5C93F9DF" box="[1116,1172,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">et al.</emphasis>
(2018) support them as part of a Clade Called 
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFE38F9CD59C5F93A" box="[392,450,1663,1686]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Cora</emphasis>
s.s., grouping 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFDD6F9CD5AF7F93A" authorityName="McLachlan" authorityYear="1881" box="[614,752,1663,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Polythoridae" genus="Cora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jocosa">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFDD6F9CD5AF7F93A" box="[614,752,1663,1686]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Cora jocosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MCLaChlan, 1881), 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFC6DF9CD5CFBF93B" authority="(Selys, 1853)" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1853" baseAuthorityName="Selys" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[989,1276,1662,1687]" class="Insecta" family="Polythoridae" genus="Cora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyane">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFC6DF9CD5C58F93A" box="[989,1119,1663,1686]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Cora cyane</emphasis>
(Selys, 1853)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFABAF9CD591EF917" authority="Selys, 1868" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Polythoridae" genus="Cora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marina">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFABAF9CD5D9BF93A" box="[1290,1436,1663,1686]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Cora marina</emphasis>
Selys, 1868
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFE97F9115A15F917" authority="Ris, 1918" authorityName="Ris" authorityYear="1918" box="[295,530,1698,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Polythoridae" genus="Cora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irene">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFE97F91159A7F917" box="[295,416,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Cora irene</emphasis>
Ris, 1918
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFD90F9115B66F917" authority="Ris, 1918" authorityName="Ris" authorityYear="1918" box="[544,865,1698,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Polythoridae" genus="Cora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthostoma">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFD90F9115AE8F917" box="[544,751,1698,1723]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Cora xanthostoma</emphasis>
Ris, 1918
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFC27F9115BEFF917" baseAuthorityName="Selys" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[919,1000,1699,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Polythoridae" genus="Cora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inca">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFC27F9115BEFF917" box="[919,1000,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">C. inca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a Clade morphologiCally supported by the plaCement of the FW nodus Closer to the pt than to the base of the wing, and the blue Coloration on dorsum of S2. 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFF74F9595967F8AF" authorityName="Bota-Sierra &amp; Sánchez-Herrera &amp; Palacino-Rodríguez" authorityYear="2018" box="[196,352,1771,1795]" class="Insecta" family="Polythoridae" genus="Cora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verapax">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFF74F9595967F8AF" box="[196,352,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Cora verapax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the plaCement of its nodus and the blue Coloration on S2, with this Clade, whiCh Can be easily separated from the other speCies by the seCond segment of genital ligula, whiCh resembles 
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFB5CF8BD5D42F88A" box="[1260,1349,1807,1830]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFB5CF8BD5D46F88A" baseAuthorityName="Selys" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[1260,1345,1807,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Polythoridae" genus="Cora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inca">C. inca</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but the apiColateral projeCtions are wider, by its middorsal horn on apex of S10 pointing in dorsoposterior direCtion, unique among the 
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFEA4F8E55949F8C2" box="[276,334,1879,1902]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Cora</emphasis>
s.s. group. 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFE61F8E55A6AF8C2" authorityName="Bota-Sierra &amp; Sánchez-Herrera &amp; Palacino-Rodríguez" authorityYear="2018" box="[465,621,1879,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Polythoridae" genus="Cora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verapax">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFE61F8E55A6AF8C2" box="[465,621,1879,1902]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Cora verapax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has two unique CharaCteristiCs in the family 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFB2CF8E45D29F8C3" authorityName="Munz" authorityYear="1919" box="[1180,1326,1878,1903]" class="Insecta" family="Polythoridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Polythoridae</taxonomicName>
, a ventral thoraCiC tuberCle, and the abdomen almost two times longer than wings, whiCh is unusual for the family, resembling speCies of other families as 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFDC4F82C5AF0F81B" box="[628,759,1950,1975]" class="Insecta" family="Perilestidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Perilestidae</taxonomicName>
or some genera in 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFC5AF82C5C9CF81B" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1890" box="[1002,1179,1950,1975]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Coenagrionidae</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="0D8EC5F85672FFBAFB5EF82C593CF877" authority="Sjostedt, 1918" authorityName="Sjostedt" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Mesoleptobasis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F8FA62695672FFBAFB5EF82C5D9BF81B" box="[1262,1436,1950,1975]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="122">Mesoleptobasis</emphasis>
Sjöstedt, 1918
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
